South African producer-price
inflation probably slowed to 6.3 percent in May from 6.6 percent
in the previous month, according to the median estimate of nine
economists surveyed by Bloomberg.  Pretoria-based Statistics  South Africa  is due to publish
the data at 11:30 a.m. on its website.  (All events in Central African Time.) 